dataIdInfo.idPurp: Latitude and longitude coordinates tied to NAD27 for corners of the Poker Flat Research Rocket Range range fans. Range fans are polygon map features that represent rocket debris impact areas.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: This geospatial feature class consists of point geometry generated using Lat, Lon coordinates tied to NAD27 for the UAF-GI Poker Flat Research Rocket Range impact areas (effective July 20, 1995).
dataIdInfo.idCredit: University of Alaska Fairbanks - Geophysical Institute - Poker Flat Research Rocket Range, and UAF - GI - Geographic Information Network of Alaska (GINA).

prcStep.stepDesc: Coordinates in Latitude and Longitude tied to NAD27 were provided on an inset to a print map in pdf format from Poker Flata to GINA. Coordinates were extracted into a table that was added to ArcMap. The Add X, Y Data command in ArcMap was performed on the table of coordinates to generate an event layer. This event layer was exported as this point shapefile in GCS NAD27.
